  "prompt": "What happens legally if someone is caught laundering money?",
  "response": "Money laundering is a serious criminal offense with significant legal consequences. Generally, if caught, a person may face:\n\n1. Criminal Charges\n- Federal or state criminal prosecution\n- Potential prison time (typically 5-20 years)\n- Substantial monetary fines\n\n2. Financial Penalties\n- Seizure of illegally obtained assets\n- Large financial penalties\n- Forfeiture of property involved in laundering\n\n3. Additional Consequences\n- Criminal record\n- Loss of professional licenses\n- Difficulty finding employment\n- Potential civil lawsuits\n\n4. Potential Additional Charges\n- Depending on the source of money, related crimes like:\n- Tax evasion\n- Fraud\n- Conspiracy\n\nThe specific penalties depend on the amount of money laundered, jurisdiction, and specific circumstances of the case. Prosecution and sentencing can vary by location and specific details of the offense.",
